You might need to install xacro with:

sudo apt install ros-jazzy-xacro




--ros2 run robot_state_publisher robot_state_publisher --ros-args -p robot_description:="$(xacro my_robot.urdf)"




might need to install

sudo apt install ros-jazzy-joint-state-publisher-gui

--ros2 run joint_state_publisher_gui joint_state_publisher_gui



--ros2 run rviz2 rviz3



Steps

--mkdir ros2_ws
--cd ros2_ws
--mkdir src

"should not be necessary"
--sudo apt install ros-dev-tools

--colcon build
--source install/setup.bash
--gedit ~/.bashrc

at the bottom of the file you need to source your new ros2 workspace

add
"source ~/ros2_ws/install/setup.bash"

inside the source folder lets build a package now
--ros2 pkg create my_robot_description
--cd my_robot_description
--rm -rf include/ src/
--mkdir urdf

lets move our urdf robot inside the urdf directory we created

--cd 
--mv my_robot.urdf ros2_ws/src/my_robot_description/urdf/

go back to the src directory of our new package
--cd ros2_ws/src

open visual studio code
--code .

inside the CMakeList.txt file lets install the urdf
Add the following under "find_package()"

--install(
  DIRECTORY urdf
  DESTINATION share/${PROJECT_NAME}/
)

go back to the workspace and do another build
--colcon build

lets create a launch file now

create a "launch" directory inside your robot description package at the same level of the urdf directory.

modify the CMakeList.txt fiel and add the launch directory.

--install(
  DIRECTORY urdf launch
  DESTINATION share/${PROJECT_NAME}/
)

create a new file inside the launch directory named display.launch.xml

Lets conver the urdf to sacro format for more complexity and prep for gazebo

add .xacro at the end of the .urdf file name


Inertial -- its important to understand

formulas etc...  there is a good wikipedia page.




-- ros2 run teleop_twist_keyboard teleop_twist_keyboard
